HEADWORD: Anaglyptography
<hw>An`a*glyp*tog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/ embossed + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art of copying works
in relief, or of engraving as to give the subject an embossed or raised
appearance; -- used in representing coins, bas-reliefs, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

